Observations¶

The average RAM consumption was about 700MB, the CPU was fully loaded. By the end of the test SWAP was fully utilized. There were rare PostgresQL errors associated with too many people wants to make an UPDATE operation:

ERROR: could not serialize access due to concurrent update
UPDATE pushers SET last_stream_ordering = 1712

However, with prolonged spam, there were periodic drops in the sending speed associated with a sharp jump in postgres load. The database process received about 100% of one core for 10-15 seconds, then again consumed about 5%.

The maximum active number of spam users was ~750 parallel connections. But it should be taken that all anti-spam and DOS protection mechanisms were disabled, otherwise, after 3-5 messages at such a speed, the method of sending the message would return an error that the request limit was exceeded.
